        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down,| Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear George</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Thanks for your very nice letter.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I fully agree to what you say about occupying yourself with small articles when you can do nothing else. It is in every way an advantage. I am far from surprised that you cannot work much at mathematicks—my wonder is that you can any day in your present state.— What an evil it is about the cold Lecture room. Oh my eye there is such a paper by Maxwell Clerk in yesterday’s Nature!<ref target="#foot.f3"/> It has been horribly cold; yesterday I could not anyhow keep warm.</p>
<p>It is a fearfully difficult moral problem about the speaking out on religion, &amp; I have never been able to make up my mind.— I asked Dicey &amp; Litchfield, when they were talking about J. S. Mill’s reticence, but got no answer from them.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/> As I am sure Hen.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> would like to read your nice letter, I will send it her by this post.— We were delighted to get a good account of Horace<ref target="#foot.f6"/> from himself this morning,—give the dear old fellow my love.—</p>
<p>Yours affect<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> | Ch Darwin</p>
<p>We have had an Irishman a grand Breeder of Short-Horns here to Luncheon—he declares that my Books have been of great use to him in breeding!<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.5 in yesterday’s] ‘in’ <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘at’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
